#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cedocs-integration.md:93
msgid "Worker lifecycle"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cedocs-integration.md:95
msgid ""
"The worker is started inside the `app.listen()` callback in `packages/"
"backend/src/index.ts` and stopped cleanly in both `SIGTERM` and `SIGINT` "
"handlers. It will not start polling until the HTTP server is fully bound."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cedocs-integration.md:99
msgid "Stub mode"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cedocs-integration.md:101
msgid ""
"When `EDOCS_STUB_MODE=true` (the default), all `EdocsService` methods return "
"realistic fake responses and log what they would have done. The worker, "
"routes, and BPMN process behave identically — the stub is fully transparent "
"to callers."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cedocs-integration.md:103
msgid ""
"This allows the complete RIP Phase 1 process to run end-to-end in "
"development and acceptance environments before a live eDOCS server is "
"available."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cedocs-integration.md:105
msgid ""
"To switch to a live server, set `EDOCS_STUB_MODE=false` and provide real "
"credentials. No code changes are required."
msgstr ""

